It is the third in the sequence of the [[Sexagenary cycle]], following [[乙丑|Otsuchū]] and preceding [[丁卯|Teibō]]. In the [[Yin-yang and the Five Elements|Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory]], the [[Heavenly Stems|stem]] 丙 represents Yang and Fire, while the [[Earthly Branches|branch]] 寅 represents Yang and Wood, forming a [[Five Elements#Mutual Generation|mutual generation (Wood generates Fire)]] relationship.
==Pronunciation== * English: Yang Fire Tiger (丙寅) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): bǐngyín ** Cantonese (Jyutping): bing3 jan4 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi 1: Hinoe-tora ***Kunyomi 2: Heika-no-tora ***Onyomi 1: Heiin ** Korean (Revised Romanization, Hangul): byeongin (병인) ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Bính Dần
<!-- == * Yang Fire Tiger (丙寅) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): bǐngyín ** Cantonese (Jyutping): beng2 jan4 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi: ひのえとら (hinoe-tora) ***Onyomi: へいかのとら (heika-no-tora) ***Onyomi: へいいん (heiin) ** Korean (Revised Romanization): byeongin ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Bính Dần
--> ==Years of Yang Fire Tiger== A year is classified as Heiin if its [[Gregorian calendar|Western calendar]] year, when divided by 60, leaves a remainder of 6. {| class="wikitable" |+'''Heiin Years''' |- ![[1st millennium]]!![[2nd millennium]]!![[3rd millennium]] |- | *[[6]] *[[66]] *[[:en:126|126]] *[[186]] *[[246]] *[[306]] *[[366]] *[[426]] *[[486]] *[[546]] *[[606]] *[[666]] *[[726]] *[[786]] *[[846]] *[[906]] *[[966]] | *[[:en:1026|1026]] *[[:en:1086|1086]] *[[:en:1146|1146]] *[[:en:1206|1206]] *[[:en:1266|1266]] *[[:en:1326|1326]] *[[:en:1386|1386]] *[[:en:1446|1446]] *[[:en:1506|1506]] *[[:en:1566|1566]] *[[1626]] *[[1686]] *[[1746]] *[[1806]] *[[1866]] *[[1926]] *[[1986]] | *[[2046]] *[[2106]] *[[2166]] *[[2226]] *[[2286]] *[[2346]] *[[2406]] *[[2466]] *[[2526]] *[[2586]] *[[2646]] *[[2706]] *[[2766]] *[[2826]] *[[2886]] *[[2946]] |}
==Months of Yang Fire Tiger== The first month (January) of a year ending in 4 or 9 in the Western calendar (when the [[Heavenly Stems|stem]] is [[甲|Kō]] or [[己|Ki]]) is designated as a Heiin month. However, this is based on the [[Chinese lunar calendar|lunar calendar]] or the [[solar term calendar]], where the month may start from [[Lìchūn|Risshun]] to the day before [[Jingzhe|Keichitsu]].
==Days of Yang Fire Tiger== === Rekichū (Lower Section) === Heiin days in the [[Lower Section rekichū]] are as follows: * [[Unlucky Meeting Days]] (for the [[Chinese lunar calendar|lunar]] months of 3 and 9) == See Also == *{{prefix|qq=}} *{{intitle|qq=}}
