It is the third in the sequence of the [[Sexagenary cycle]], following [[乙丑|Otsuchū]] and preceding [[丁卯|Teibō]]. In the [[Yin-yang and the Five Elements|Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory]], the [[Heavenly Stems|stem]] 丙 represents Yang and Fire, while the [[:en:Earthly Branches|branch]] 寅 represents Yang and Wood, forming a [[Five Elements#Mutual Generation|mutual generation (Wood generates Fire)]] relationship.
==Pronunciation== * English: Yang Fire Tiger (丙寅) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): bǐngyín ** Cantonese (Jyutping): bing3 jan4 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi 1: Hinoe-tora ***Kunyomi 2: Heika-no-tora ***Onyomi 1: Heiin ** Korean (Revised Romanization, Hangul): byeongin (병인) ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Bính Dần
