==Months of Yang Fire Tiger== The first month (January) of a year ending in 4 or 9 in the Western calendar (when the [[Heavenly Stems|stem]] is [[甲|Kō]] or [[:en:己|Ki]]) is designated as a Heiin month. However, this is based on the [[:en:Chinese lunar calendar|lunar calendar]] or the [[solar term calendar]], where the month may start from [[Lìchūn|Risshun]] to the day before [[Jingzhe|Keichitsu]].
==Days of Yang Fire Tiger== === Rekichū (Lower Section) === Heiin days in the [[Lower Section rekichū]] are as follows: * [[Unlucky Meeting Days]] (for the [[:en:Chinese lunar calendar|lunar]] months of 3 and 9) == See Also == *{{prefix|qq=}} *{{intitle|qq=}}
